Class TupleFactory<A extends DataObject,AF extends DataObjectFactory<A>,T extends TupleFactory.Tuple<A>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.AbstractContexed

  • Type Parameters:
    A - type of DataObject
    AF - type of DataObjectFactory
    T - type of TupleFactory.Tuple
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Contexed, Targetted<T>

    public class TupleFactory<A extends DataObject,AF extends DataObjectFactory<A>,T extends TupleFactory.Tuple<A>>
extends AbstractContexed
implements Targetted<T>
    Factory for sets of DataObjects generated by a join. Each result in the join becomes a tuple. Where a record from one of the contributing tables appears in multiple results from the join it also appears in multiple tuples.
